"},{"content":"Place water and stock paste into mixing bowl and bring to the boil <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add polenta and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add oil, thyme, paprika, pepper and 250 g of the reserved ricotta and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Spoon polenta mixture into prepared tin, smooth surface and place into refrigerator to set (approx. 30 minutes)."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Remove set polenta from tin and slice into thick chips (2 x 9 cm). Place onto prepared baking tray. Sprinkle with reserved Parmesan cheese, drizzle with extra olive oil and bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) until cheese has melted and chips are golden brown. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This recipe uses coarser cornmeal polenta, not instant polenta.","Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 20m","4 portions"]}